member.name: T:Zebra.Savanna.CreateBarcode
member.summary: Provides access to the Savanna barcode creation APIs.

member.name: M:Zebra.Savanna.CreateBarcode.CreateAsync(Zebra.Savanna.Symbology,System.String,System.Int32,Zebra.Savanna.Rotation,System.Boolean)
member.summary: Generates a barcode from the text provided and returns a PNG image
member.param: The barcode symbology.

The data or text to include in the generated barcode. Usually an error will occur when the barcode symbology cannot support the text provided. Different symbology allow for numbers only, or alpha-numeric, or uppercase alphabets, and some restrict characters. For example: code39 only accepts numbers and uppercase letters.
Sets both the x-axis and the y-axis scaling factors. Must be an integer > 0. Use if you want default X & Y, just different size. short.
Rotates the barcode in 90 degree increments.

Allows for the data included in the barcode to be printed in human readable form with the barcode (usually printed text under the linear barcode, this setting is ignored for many 2D symbologies such as qrcode).

member.name: M:Zebra.Savanna.CreateBarcode.CreateAsync(Zebra.Savanna.Symbology,System.String,System.Int32,System.Int32,Zebra.Savanna.Rotation,System.Boolean)
member.summary: Generates a barcode from the text provided and returns a PNG image
member.param: The barcode symbology.

The data or text to include in the generated barcode. Usually an error will occur when the barcode symbology cannot support the text provided. Different symbology allow for numbers only, or alpha-numeric, or uppercase alphabets, and some restrict characters. For example: code39 only accepts numbers and uppercase letters.

Sets the x-axis. Must be an integer > 0. Use with scaleY, if using scale only, leave scaleX & scaleY blank. Allows proportional changes to the resulting barcode, helpful with linear barcodes to make tall or short.
Sets the y-axis scaling factors. Must be an integer > 0. Use with scaleX.
Rotates the barcode in 90 degree increments.

Allows for the data included in the barcode to be printed in human readable form with the barcode (usually printed text under the linear barcode, this setting is ignored for many 2D symbologies such as qrcode).

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Classification.ClassI
member.summary: Dangerous or defective products that predictably could cause serious health problems or death. Examples include: food found to contain botulinum toxin, food with undeclared allergens, a label mix-up on a lifesaving drug, or a defective artificial heart valve.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Classification.ClassII
member.summary: Products that might cause a temporary health problem, or pose only a slight threat of a serious nature. Example: a drug that is under-strength but that is not used to treat life-threatening situations.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Classification.ClassIII
member.summary: Products that are unlikely to cause any adverse health reaction, but that violate FDA labeling or manufacturing laws. Examples include: a minor container defect and lack of English labeling in a retail food.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.OpenFDAProduct.PharmClassCS
member.summary: Chemical structure classification of the drug product’s pharmacologic class. Takes the form of the classification, followed by `[Chemical/Ingredient]` (such as `Thiazides [Chemical/Ingredient]` or `Antibodies, Monoclonal [Chemical/Ingredient].

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.OpenFDAProduct.PharmClassEPC
member.summary: Established pharmacologic class associated with an approved indication of an active moiety (generic drug) that the FDA has determined to be scientifically valid and clinically meaningful. Takes the form of the pharmacologic class, followed by `[EPC]` (such as `Thiazide Diuretic [EPC]` or `Tumor Necrosis Factor Blocker [EPC]`.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.OpenFDAProduct.PharmClassPE
member.summary: Physiologic effect or pharmacodynamic effect—tissue, organ, or organ system level functional activity of the drug’s established pharmacologic class. Takes the form of the effect, followed by `[PE]` (such as `Increased Diuresis [PE]` or `Decreased Cytokine Activity [PE]`.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.OpenFDAProduct.pharm_class_moa
member.summary: Mechanism of action of the drug—molecular, subcellular, or cellular functional activity—of the drug’s established pharmacologic class. Takes the form of the mechanism of action, followed by `[MoA]` (such as `Calcium Channel Antagonists [MoA]` or `Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor Blocking Activity [MoA]`.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.OpenFDAProduct.ProductNDC

member.summary: The postal code in which the recalling firm is located.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.ProductCode
member.summary: A three-letter identifier assigned to a product category. Assignment is based upon the product classification designated under 21 CFR Parts 862-892, and the technology and intended use of the product. Occasionally these codes are changed over time.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.ProductDescription
member.summary: Brief description of the product being recalled.

member.summary: The amount of defective product subject to recall.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.ProductType
member.summary: The type of product being recalled. For drug queries, this will always be `Drugs`.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.ReasonForRecall
member.summary: Information describing how the product is defective and violates the FD&C Act or related statutes.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.RecallInitiationDate
member.summary: Date that the firm first began notifying the public or their consignees of the recall.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.RecallNumber
member.summary: A numerical designation assigned by FDA to a specific recall event used for tracking purposes.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.RecallingFirm
member.summary: The firm that initiates a recall or, in the case of an FDA requested recall or FDA mandated recall, the firm that has primary responsibility for the manufacture and (or) marketing of the product to be recalled.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.ReportDate
member.summary: Date that the FDA issued the enforcement report for the product recall.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.State
member.summary: The U.S. state in which the recalling firm is located.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.Status
member.summary: The status of a recall (pending, ongoing, completed, or terminated).

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.TerminationDate
member.summary: Date that the FDA terminated the enforcement report for the product recall.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Product.VoluntaryMandated
member.summary: Describes who initiated the recall. Recalls are almost always voluntary, meaning initiated by a firm. A recall is deemed voluntary when the firm voluntarily removes or corrects marketed products or the FDA requests the marketed products be removed or corrected. A recall is mandated when the firm was ordered by the FDA to remove or correct the marketed products, under section 518(e) of the FD&C Act, National Childhood Vaccine Injury Act of 1986, 21 CFR 1271.440, Infant Formula Act of 1980 and its 1986 amendments, or the Food Safety Modernization Act (FSMA).

member.name: T:Zebra.Savanna.Models.ProductType
member.summary: The type of product being recalled (drug, device, or food).

member.summary: The recalled product is a drug product.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.ProductType.Devices
member.summary: The recalled product is a device product.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.ProductType.Food
member.summary: The recalled product is a food product.

member.name: P:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Recall`1.Results
member.summary: A of matching records.

member.name: T:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Status
member.summary: The status of a recall (pending, ongoing, completed, or terminated).

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Status.Ongoing
member.summary: A recall which is currently in progress.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Status.Completed
member.summary: The recall action reaches the point at which the firm has actually retrieved and impounded all outstanding product that could reasonably be expected to be recovered, or has completed all product corrections.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Status.Terminated
member.summary: FDA has determined that all reasonable efforts have been made to remove or correct the violative product in accordance with the recall strategy, and proper disposition has been made according to the degree of hazard.

member.name: F:Zebra.Savanna.Models.Status.Pending
member.summary: Actions that have been determined to be recalls, but that remain in the process of being classified.
